OL,3,CMore people can now apply for social
OL,4,Chousing in Jersey
OL,6,FMore people can now apply for social
OL,7,Fhomes in under new rules announced by
OL,8,Fthe Housing Minister, Deputy Sam Mezec.
OL,10,FThe minimum age has been lowered from
OL,11,F35 to 30 for those without children,
OL,12,Fwith plans to reduce it further to 25
OL,13,Flater this year.
OL,15,FThe maximum yearly income threshold
OL,16,Ffor a one-bed home has also been
OL,17,Fraised from #32,300 to #38,818 for a
OL,18,Fsingle person and from #40,700 to
OL,19,F#52,462 for joint applicants.
